					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The problem with using VRAM as RAM is...<br /><br />1. it's slow. You have to wait till v-blank or turn rendering off to access it.<br /><br />2. It might cripple your ability to scroll, if you are using nametable VRAM.<br /><br />3. It's non-standard to the official NES games. If you are doing something beyond what actual games did, why not just make a modern game?</div>

					
						<div class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://nesdoug.com" class="postlink">nesdoug.com</a> -- blog/tutorial on programming for the NES</div>
