						<div class="postbody">I don't see any problems in using VRAM as general RAM, if the limited access is not a problem.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle">dougeff wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">3. It's non-standard to the official NES games.</div><br />This is bullshit. If there was no innovation, every NES game ever would look like Balloon Fight, and there'd be no mappers using the cartridge port's signals in creative ways.<br /><br />Also, there have been cases of NES games from back in the day using video memory for other purposes, such as SMB and some CNROM games storing miscellaneous data in CHR-ROM or battery-backed CHR-RAM being used to save games.</div>

