						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">dougeff wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">then maybe NES isn't the best platform. SNES has standard 128k RAM, and you can still use mode zero if you REALLY want it to look like an NES game.</div><br />As <a href="https://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=163300#p163300" class="postlink">you and I both wrote elsewhere</a>, people who spend money on a Super NES Game Pak expect the graphics to look no less detailed than those of launch title <em>Super Mario World</em>. I doubt there is much interest in Super NES games that use <em>only</em> the increased RAM, not the increased graphical capability.</div>

